            <P></P><BR>
            <P class=3Dsection>Specifications</P>
            <P>Design and code a class that holds information about a =
bank=20
            customer's account.&nbsp; Upon instantiation, an object =
assumes a=20
            safe empty state.&nbsp; Your design includes the following =
member=20
            functions:=20
            <UL>
              <LI><SPAN class=3Dcode>void open(long)</SPAN> that =
receives a=20
              customer number and opens an account for that customer.=20
              <LI><SPAN class=3Dcode>double balance() const</SPAN> that =
returns=20
              the current balance in the account.=20
              <LI><SPAN class=3Dcode>double interestEarned() =
const</SPAN> that=20
              returns the interest earned in the account.=20
              <LI><SPAN class=3Dcode>void transaction(double)</SPAN> =
that receives=20
              an amount - positive valued for a deposit and negative =
valued for=20
              a withdrawal - and adjusts the account balance.=20
              <LI><SPAN class=3Dcode>void dailyInterest()</SPAN> =
calculates the=20
              interest earned in a single day and adds that interest to =
the=20
              interest earned since the most recent compounding.=20
              <LI><SPAN class=3Dcode>void compound()</SPAN> compounds =
the interest=20
              earned to date with the current balance and reset the =
interest=20
              earned to date to 0.=20
              <LI><SPAN class=3Dcode>double rate()</SPAN> returns the =
interest=20
              rate payable to any customer.=20
              <LI><SPAN class=3Dcode>void setRate(double)</SPAN> =
receives an=20
              interest rate and sets the interest rate payable to all =
customers=20
              to that rate.&nbsp; </LI></UL>Make those member functions =
inline=20
            where it makes sense to do so.&nbsp; Store your class =
declaration in=20
            a header file named <SPAN class=3Dcode>Account.h</SPAN> and =
your=20
            implementation in a file named <SPAN=20
            class=3Dcode>Account.cpp</SPAN>.&nbsp;=20
            <P></P>
            <P>Write a main program that uses your class and performs =
the=20
            following:=20
            <UL>
              <LI>sets the interest rate at 2.5%=20
              <LI>opens an account for customer with the number =
123456789=20
              <LI>deposits $1000 in the customer's account=20
              <LI>calculates the interest earned for 30 days=20
              <LI>compounds the interest earned with the current balance =

              <LI>changes the interest rate to 3.0%=20
